{
  "stem": "1363.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Where is he now?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, it-- I went back to the star house, thinking that he might have been, lost our way.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was in the morning, about 11 o'clock. 10, 11 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I couldn't find him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went back again later in the afternoon and looked, already, on bodies, whether I'd find him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't find him anywhere.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what I heard, that those bodies which were found in the last few days, on the street, they threw them into a mikveh.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a mikveh, that was a Jewish-- in the ghetto, was a mikveh, and they put all those bodies.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, I looked everywhere for-- for Freddy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I looked on the streets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I looked in the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In the Jewish [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] synagogue, they had the garden there, and they dug in through these ghetto areas, certain bodies, and they put the name outside.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I couldn't find him there either.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, even to the very day, I think what happened was, that when he left Grandma and Auntie in the ghetto two days earlier, on the way home to his place where he was sleeping, he got a shrapnel, which killed him.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they found the body and they threw it into the mikveh.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know because that was the only place I didn't look for him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I couldn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, that was already the, the liberation by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then we had some hard times as far as food is concerned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Grandma and the little girl had got a sickness, which is diphtheria.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know, it's a runner of the bowels, and they had-- we had to have either rice or potatoes for them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now that didn't exist in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
